[[File:Kim Seokju.PNG|thumb|right|Gim Seokju]] {{Infobox Korean name |hangul={{linktext|김|석|주}} |hanja={{linktext|金|錫|冑|}} |rr=Gim Seog-ju |mr=Kim Sŏkchu |hangulja=사백 |hanjaja={{linktext|斯|百|}} |rrja=Sabaek |mrja=Sabaek |hangulho=식암 |hanjaho={{linktext|息|庵|}} |rrho=Sigam |mrho=Sigam }}
'''Gim Seokju''' ([[Korea]]n: 김석주, [[hanja]]: 金錫冑, 1634 &ndash; September 20, 1684) was one of the [[Neo-Confucianism|Neo-Confucian]] scholars, politicians and writers of the [[Korea]]n [[Joseon Dynasty]]. His nickname was '''Sigam''' (식암, 息庵), a [[courtesy name]] was '''Sabaek''' (사백, 斯百).<ref>[http://100.naver.com/100.nhn?docid=31181 Gim Seokju:Naver] {{ko}}</ref> He was a cousin of [[Queen Myunseong]].<ref>wife of 18th king [[Hyunjong of Joseon]], mother of 19th king [[Sukjong of Joseon]]</ref> He was [[prime minister]] of the Joseon Dynasty in 1680.
==Books== * 'Shikamjip' (식암집, 息庵集) * 'Beolgo' (별고, 別稿) * 'Haedongsabu' (해동사부, 海東辭賦) * 'Shikamyugo' (식암유고, 息菴遺稿) * 'Hanggunsooji' (행군수지, 行軍須知) * 'Gomunbaiksun' (고문백선, 古文白選) * 'Hangoojasu' (한구자수, 韓構字藪) * Chunsojhajipseomun (춘소자집 서문, 春沼子集 序文)
